[Tox](https://tox.chat/) is a p2p message protocol with several client implementations. Some fact about it:
1. It is secure and decentralized. It supports text chat, group chat, audio, video and file transfers;
2. It supports tunneling through tor;
3. The p2p part uses DHT and asymmetric encryption;
4. On the lower level users are identified by a hash like string but you can use naming servers to get a name like "lala@toxme.io";
5. I used to think it was an abandoned project but it actually only went through a friendly fork and now is being developed by [TokTok](https://toktok.ltd/index.html);
6. It's probably available on your distros repositories, search for "qtox", the main GUI desktop client. 

